# 4. もうひとつの始業式

Saki: Humhumhuum♪
Miku: <Sounds like you're in a good mood, Saki.>
Saki: I am! I mean, today was just so much fun!
Saki: I was a little anxious about what my new class was gonna look like, but it ended up feeling like a nice, fresh start!
Honami: I agree. It was also nice to see some familiar faces.
???: Excellent! Then, that's mission accomplished!
Ichika: Huh...?
Honami: I thought I heard a familiar voice just now...
Tsukasa: Ah, Saki, everyone!!!
Saki: Oh, Tsukasa!
Ichika: *Gasp* Miku, hide!
Miku: <Hiding.>
Tsukasa: What are the odds that we'd run into each other here?!
Ichika: N-Not very high! What brings you here today, Tsukasa...?
Tsukasa: I was just buying some running shoes. The pair I was wearing reached its limit during practice the other day.
Saki: Oh, you mentioned that earlier this morning! Did you find a pair you like?
Tsukasa: Yes, and they're a perfect fit! I was just heading home in the highest of spirits!
Honami: Which explains why you said, “Mission accomplished,” just now.
Shiho: Is “mission” really the right word for that...?
Tsukasa: Anyway, how were things at Miya Girls? The opening ceremony was today, yes?
Saki: It was super fun! Also, guess what? Shiho and I are in the same class♪
Tsukasa: Ah, that's wonderful to hear! I hope you won't mind keeping an eye on her for me, Shiho!
Shiho: Uh, sure...
Tsukasa: The opening ceremony for my school was also today. It ended up being quite the spectacle.
Saki: Wait, really? What was it like?
Tsukasa: Well, where do I begin...? First, when I headed over to my new class...
Tsukasa: Whaaaaaaaaaaaaaaat?!
Tsukasa: H-How...?! Can it be...?!
Tsukasa: I'm in the same class as you, Rui?!
Rui: Well, this is quite the surprise.
Rui: I'd heard rumors about naughty children being placed in separate classes in order to make things easier for the teachers.
Tsukasa: I see... Wait, naughty children?
Rui: (In all likelihood, they decided it'd be easier to keep an eye on us if we were in the same class since we're seen together quite a lot.)
Classmates: Geez, they put the Weirdo Wombo Combo in the same class...?
Classmates: How is this okay...? I don't even wanna think about what's gonna happen during class...
Classmates: This could be interesting. They do always seem to have fun together.
Tsukasa: Hm? We seem to be attracting quite a bit of attention.
Tsukasa: Does this mean...?
Tsukasa: Do my classmates know a star when they see one?! Are they that entranced by my aura?!
Rui: Hmm... That could be one reason...
Rui: In any case, I'm glad that we're classmates. Let's do our best this year leading up to our graduation, Tsukasa.
Tsukasa: Yes! Let's do our best!
Tsukasa: Now, as for the opening ceremony... I was about to head over, but we seem to still have some time.
Tsukasa: Wait, of course! Why don't we go over to see Nene?
Rui: Hm? Nene?
Tsukasa: Yes. She didn't sound very excited about her new class during practice the other day. I was thinking that we could help her relax if she's still feeling nervous.
Rui: Hmm... I'm not sure us visiting her class is going to make her feel any better...
Rui: But it may be worth taking a look. I am interested in seeing what her class is like.
Tsukasa: Yes, that's what I like to hear! Let's head over to the second-year classrooms!
